                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270111-64-off365 t18270111-64-crimeloc367"></join> - I was there on the 11th of December, and saw the prisoner come in without an umbrella; I watched him, and saw him go out; I followed him - he ran across the yard, and dropped this umbrella; I secured him, and found on him forty duplicates; ten for umbrellas, one for a parasol, and the rest for coats, waistcoats, and other articles; most of the umbrellas have been claimed.</p>
               <p>
            
